        {
          "i": "rich_note-01805711-1294-41d8-9a4b-956d46fa77e3",
          "x": 0,
          "y": 2,
          "w": 40,
          "h": 9,
          "state": {
            "storage": {
              "html": "<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">How To Use</h2><p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Congress number is a sequential number representing the formed Congress for the elected period. As of 2026, the current Congress number is 119. Leaving empty will populate the 100 most recent actions.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">You can narrow the field by selecting a bill type, restricting dates, or adjusting the limit and offset parameters.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">The 3 widgets on this tab are grouped by the \"Bill URL\" column.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>NOTE: Clicking on the cell in the whitespace beside \"Link\" will change the loaded bill in the two widgets below. Don't click the Link directly, but click to the right of it.</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>You can also use shorthand to manually enter bills - `{congress}/{bill_type}/{bill_number}`</strong></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Some bills may not have any formal text, directly, such as resolutions. If it has not been introduced in the House, it will likely not have any text to display for the viewer. Items from today may not be immediately available to the public via API.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p><p></p>"
            }
          },
          "groups": []
        }
      ]
    },
